  "prompt": "What are the strongest majors in terms of job prospects and what are the weakest majors at Woodbury University?",
  "response": "Woodbury University offers a variety of academic programs, each with different job prospects. Generally speaking, stronger majors in terms of job prospects at many universities typically include fields such as:\n\n1. Business Administration\n2. Architecture\n3. Computer Science\n4. Interior Design\n5. Animation\n6. Marketing\n7. Graphic Design\n\nThese fields generally have higher demand in the job market and typically offer good earning potential and career growth opportunities.\n\nWeaker majors in terms of job prospects can be more subjective and might vary based on changing industry trends and economic conditions. However, majors that traditionally can have lower immediate job prospects include:\n\n1. Fine Arts \n2. Philosophy\n3. History\n4. Sociology\n5. English Literature\n\nThese fields don't always align directly with high-demand industries, which can make it more challenging to find employment immediately after graduation without additional specialization or further studies.\n\nIt's important to note that the strength of job prospects can vary widely based on personal interests, geographic location, economic conditions, networking, and other factors. Students should consult the career services at Woodbury University and research specific industries to get a better understanding of the current job market for their intended majors.",
